    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-01T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-01T05:00:00-05:00" n="55"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/47</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé d’Affaires in Sweden</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_CJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Stockholm</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-01T11:00:00+01:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 1, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6:35 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Member of German Legation informs me confidentially Germany endeavoring to
                    persuade Sweden to readjust<note n="1" xml:id="d55fn1">Garbled in transmission:
                        should read “attack Russia.” See the Chargé’s dispatch No. 433 of July 31
                        (received September 4), <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, p.<ref target="#pg_88"
                            >88</ref>.</note> in case of general war. Sympathies here with
                    Germany.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
